# UniPilot AI

UniPilot AI is an AI-powered academic decision support platform. The project is graded mainly on **backend quality**, not frontend design.

## Mandatory Requirements
- App must run first try with Docker (`docker compose up --build` from a clean clone).
- `README.md` must explain how to run the app and the tests.
- Use at least two backend containers.
- Only the API/web container may be exposed to clients.
- MongoDB, Redis, worker, and AI service must stay internal.
- Store persistent data in MongoDB.
- Never store passwords in plain text; hash with bcrypt.
- Use JWT authentication; protect student-specific endpoints.
- Validate all request bodies.
- Add rate limiting to auth and AI endpoints.
- Use async/background processing for long AI requests (Redis queue + worker).
- Add unit, integration, E2E/system, stress, and security tests (coverage ≥ 80%).
- Regular GitHub commits from all team members.
- Deliver a final project report and risk assessment.

## Work Style
- Work **feature by feature**. Do not implement the whole project at once.
- After each feature: add tests, update the README, and commit.

## Required Pre-Work Context
- Before any **major implementation work** (new feature, architecture change, refactor across services), read:
  1. `docs/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` (primary source of truth)
  2. `docs/planning/IMPLEMENTATION_PHASES.md` (phase guardrails)
  3. `docs/planning/FEATURE_BACKLOG.md` (feature order/priorities)
- If implementation reality changes, update `docs/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` in the same work cycle.

## Workflow System
Reusable prompts (run in order per feature) live in `.cursor/prompts/`:
1. `01-explore-repo.md` — understand current state
2. `02-plan-feature.md` — plan one feature
3. `03-implement-feature.md` — TDD implementation
4. `04-write-tests.md` — full test suite
5. `05-security-review.md` — security checklist
6. `06-docker-check.md` — first-run Docker verification
7. `07-readme-update.md` — keep README accurate
8. `08-risk-assessment.md` — risk report
9. `09-final-demo-prep.md` — submission checklist

